Vietson:<br><br>
Don't take the Vietnamese perspectives on history too lightly.  I would suspect that you will find a great deal of truth in some of those accounts.<br>
I am embarrassed to know so little about Viet Nam's history. It may be that Mr. Diem did favor a united Viet Nam.  That would be an interesting question to answer.  Would he have accepted a united Viet Nam at any cost... even Communist domination?  That may answer your question..Why he was killed.  Were there other Vietnamese who simply wanted the seat of power and colaborated against him?  It is prudent to assume that if the CIA influence was working... one must consider the opposition's efforts during these early stages.<br><br>
Best to you and yours,<br><br>
